<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1740,1947]" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,325,1740,1766]" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">Discussion:</emphasis>
—This new 
<taxonomicName box="[461,575,1741,1766]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Pitcairnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[461,575,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">Pitcairnia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Carriere 1881: 390) Andre (1888: 565)" authorityName="Andre" authorityPageNumber="565" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Carriere" baseAuthorityPageNumber="390" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[699,1324,1740,1767]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Pitcairnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[699,879,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">Pitcairnia nigra</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carriere, E. A." box="[892,1106,1740,1766]" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" pagination="390 - 391" refId="ref2284" refString="Carriere, E. A. (1881) Neumannia nigra. Revue Horticole 53: 390 - 391." type="journal article" year="1881">Carrierè 1881: 390</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E. F." box="[1118,1324,1740,1767]" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" pagination="563 - 568" refId="ref2117" refString="Andre, E. F. (1888). Enumeration des Bromeliacees, recoltees en 1875 - 1876 dans l'Amerique du Sud. Revue Hortic 60: 563 - 568." type="journal article" year="1888">André (1888: 565)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
principally in the characteristic color of the petals (very dark purple), leaf and inflorescence 
<typeStatus box="[1038,1089,1777,1803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
, but differs from it by its shorter floral bracts (
<quantity box="[289,386,1812,1839]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
) and pedicels up to 
<quantity box="[620,687,1812,1839]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long vs. floral bracts longer (
<quantity box="[1029,1153,1812,1839]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="72.5" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="65.0">65–80 mm</quantity>
long) and sessile flowers. 
<taxonomicName box="[136,352,1848,1874]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Pitcairnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albifolia">
<emphasis box="[136,352,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">Pitcairnia albifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has homomorphic leaves, up to 
<quantity box="[717,786,1848,1875]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="cm" value="16.0">16 cm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity box="[874,957,1848,1875]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 cm</quantity>
wide, with entire petioles; while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Carriere" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1363,1452,1849,1874]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Pitcairnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[1363,1452,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="48">P. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the leaves are trimorphic, 
<quantity box="[432,544,1884,1911]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="cm" value="63.5" valueMax="67.0" valueMin="60.0">60–67 cm</quantity>
long × 
<quantity box="[634,747,1884,1911]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="48" unit="cm" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10–14 cm</quantity>
wide, with stout serrate petioles. The specimen did not match any of the other known taxon in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
